This article is a statement by the President on Senator Tim Johnson, who has dedicated himself to improving the lives of South Dakota's working families for over three decades. The President highlights Johnson's work in protecting the environment, empowering rural and Native American communities, and building a better financial system. The President also mentions Johnson's return to the Senate floor after a life-threatening brain injury, which continues to inspire others. The President expresses his intention to work with Senator Johnson as he finishes his third term and sends well wishes to Johnson and his family.